19:37.010 --> 19:38.852
Friend, I don't know what brought you here.

19:38.932 --> 19:41.756
I don't know where you're at in terms of your relationship with God.

19:42.336 --> 19:46.381
But I do know that there is hope and that there is a God who loves you.

19:46.401 --> 19:55.891
And here in this Advent season, if we can focus on Him, the greatest gift ever offered to us by His grace, we can experience His love and be made new.

19:55.972 --> 19:56.232
Amen?

19:57.153 --> 19:57.934
Well, let's pray together.

19:58.334 --> 20:01.778
Father, as we celebrate this Advent season, we're just so grateful

20:02.210 --> 20:04.132
For the gift of love, that is Jesus.

20:04.913 --> 20:11.399
And we're just mindful, Lord, that you are doing an incredible thing, calling people to yourself.

20:11.419 --> 20:18.246
And we here in this Christmas season wanna look beyond all of the pomp and circumstance that can surround this holiday season.

20:18.306 --> 20:19.667
Wonderful as it all might be.

20:19.707 --> 20:22.810
And instead, Lord, we might focus with clarity on you.

20:23.551 --> 20:26.334
And for some, that's a reminder that you've done a great work in their life.

20:26.374 --> 20:27.655
And so for that God, we're grateful.

20:27.675 --> 20:29.977
We're just grateful this Christmas season.

20:29.997 --> 20:30.898
Our hearts are full.

20:31.426 --> 20:34.131
But for others, Lord, they're still considering who you are.

20:34.151 --> 20:44.249
And may even now you warm their hearts to the truth of a God who loves them and created them in your image and called them out of darkness into light.

20:44.710 --> 20:46.212
And so we'll celebrate that together.

20:46.954 --> 20:47.635
Be glorified.

20:47.675 --> 20:53.485
I pray this Christmas season as we point to Jesus, the love of God on full display.

20:53.666 --> 20:55.589
We pray this in Jesus' name.

20:55.609 --> 20:56.050
Amen.

